#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
#: templates/admin_audit/console/hub.html
msgid "Autonomous proposals"
msgstr "Propositions autonomes"

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
msgid ""
"When armed, the system opens Courses of Action <span class=\"text-cyan\">as "
"proposals</span>, on a schedule, for action families whose track record it "
"trusts. It <span class=\"text-gold\">never</span> accepts a COA, creates a "
"task, or spends ISK — a human still commits every proposal, and every "
"proposal is audited and dismissible. Ships <span class=\"text-gold\">off</"
"span>."
msgstr ""
"Une fois armé, le système ouvre des plans d'action <span class=\"text-"
"cyan\">sous forme de propositions</span>, selon une planification, pour les "
"familles d'actions dont il juge le bilan fiable. Il n'accepte <span "
"class=\"text-gold\">jamais</span> un COA, ne crée aucune tâche et ne dépense "
"aucun ISK — un humain valide toujours chaque proposition, et chaque "
"proposition est auditée et rejetable. Livré <span class=\"text-"
"gold\">désactivé</span>."

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
msgid "Armed — the daily beat will propose for calibration-trusted families."
msgstr ""
"Armé — le beat quotidien proposera pour les familles jugées fiables par la "
"calibration."

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
msgid ""
"Disarmed — the beat fires but proposes nothing (the kill switch is off)."
msgstr ""
"Désarmé — le beat s'exécute mais ne propose rien (le coupe-circuit est "
"coupé)."

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
msgid "Arm autonomous proposal"
msgstr "Armer la proposition autonome"

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
msgid ""
"The kill switch. Off ⇒ the task returns \"disabled\" and creates nothing."
msgstr ""
"Le coupe-circuit. Coupé ⇒ la tâche renvoie « disabled » et ne crée rien."

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
msgid "Min calibration samples"
msgstr "Échantillons de calibration min."

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
msgid ""
"A family needs at least this many measured outcomes before it can be auto-"
"proposed."
msgstr ""
"Une famille doit compter au moins ce nombre de résultats mesurés avant de "
"pouvoir être proposée automatiquement."

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
msgid "Max calibration spread"
msgstr "Dispersion de calibration max."

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
msgid ""
"And its prediction-error spread must be at or below this (tighter = more "
"trusted)."
msgstr ""
"Et sa dispersion d'erreur de prédiction doit être inférieure ou égale à "
"cette valeur (plus serrée = plus fiable)."

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
msgid "Max proposals per run"
msgstr "Propositions max par exécution"

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
msgid "A hard cap on how many COAs one autonomous run may open."
msgstr "Plafond strict du nombre de COA qu'une exécution autonome peut ouvrir."

#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/autonomous.html
#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/classification.html
#: templates/admin_audit/console/command_intel/constraints.html
