#: templates/admin_audit/console/readiness/doctrines.html
msgid "Readiness · Doctrine classification"
msgstr "Préparation · Classification doctrine"

#: templates/admin_audit/console/readiness/doctrines.html
msgid ""
"Mark which doctrines are <span class=\"text-ink\">primary</span>, <span "
"class=\"text-ink\">mandatory</span> or <span class=\"text-ink\">alliance</"
"span>, set a retirement date, and a minimum pilot count. A <span "
"class=\"text-cyan\">mandatory</span> doctrine that's under-crewed raises a "
"high-severity finding; a doctrine past its <span class=\"text-"
"cyan\">retirement date</span> raises a replace-it finding. Leaving a "
"doctrine unclassified has no effect on the index."
msgstr ""
"Marquez les doctrines qui sont <span class=\"text-ink\">primary</span>, "
"<span class=\"text-ink\">mandatory</span> ou <span class=\"text-"
"ink\">alliance</span>, définissez une date de retrait et un nombre minimum "
"de pilotes. Une doctrine <span class=\"text-cyan\">mandatory</span> en sous-"
"effectif génère un constat de gravité élevée ; une doctrine ayant dépassé sa "
"<span class=\"text-cyan\">date de retrait</span> génère un constat de "
"remplacement. Laisser une doctrine non classée n'a aucun effet sur l'indice."

#: templates/admin_audit/console/readiness/doctrines.html
