#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "The programme is paused right now."
msgstr "Le programme est en pause pour le moment."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"New Cadet and Mentor registrations are closed while leadership retunes the "
"roster. You can still browse the learning tracks and check in on any "
"mentorship you already hold."
msgstr ""
"Les nouvelles inscriptions de Cadets et de Mentors sont fermées pendant que "
"la direction réajuste le roster. Vous pouvez toujours parcourir les parcours "
"d'apprentissage et suivre tout mentorat que vous avez déjà."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html templates/mentorship/register_mentor.html
msgid "Become a Veteran Mentor"
msgstr "Devenir Mentor Vétéran"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "View My Mentorship"
msgstr "Voir Mon mentorat"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Why sign up as a Cadet"
msgstr "Pourquoi s'inscrire comme Cadet"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Skip the expensive lessons."
msgstr "Évitez les leçons coûteuses."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"One hour with a veteran saves a month of dying to things you never saw "
"coming."
msgstr ""
"Une heure avec un vétéran vous épargne un mois à mourir de choses que vous "
"n'aviez pas vues venir."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "A clear path, not a firehose."
msgstr "Un chemin clair, pas un déluge d'informations."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"Field Exercises take you from docking up to holding tackle on a real fleet, "
"one step at a time."
msgstr ""
"Les Exercices de terrain vous mènent de l'amarrage au maintien du tackle sur "
"une vraie flotte, une étape à la fois."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Someone in your corner."
msgstr "Quelqu'un de votre côté."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"A name you can ping without feeling like you're bothering the whole corp."
msgstr ""
"Un nom que vous pouvez ping sans avoir l'impression de déranger toute la "
"corpo."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Earn as you learn."
msgstr "Gagnez en apprenant."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Completed exercises can pay ISK, points and recognition — see below."
msgstr ""
"Les exercices terminés peuvent rapporter des ISK, des points et de la "
"reconnaissance — voir ci-dessous."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Why mentor as a Veteran"
msgstr "Pourquoi mentorer en tant que Vétéran"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Build the fleet you want to fly with."
msgstr "Construisez la flotte avec laquelle vous voulez voler."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Every Cadet you train is another competent pilot on comms next month."
msgstr ""
"Chaque Cadet que vous formez est un pilote compétent de plus sur comms le "
"mois prochain."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Recognition that sticks."
msgstr "Une reconnaissance qui dure."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Mentor badges, certifications and standing on the leadership board."
msgstr ""
"Badges de mentor, certifications et classement sur le tableau de la "
"direction."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Light touch, real impact."
msgstr "Peu d'implication, vrai impact."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"You pick your areas, your timezone and your pace — the Grid handles the "
"matching and the paperwork."
msgstr ""
"Vous choisissez vos domaines, votre fuseau horaire et votre rythme — the "
"Grid gère la mise en relation et la paperasse."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Give back what you were given."
msgstr "Rendez ce que l'on vous a donné."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"Every veteran here was once the confused newbro asking where the undock "
"button is."
msgstr ""
"Chaque vétéran ici était autrefois le newbro perdu qui demandait où se "
"trouve le bouton undock."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Register a role"
msgstr "Inscrire un rôle"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"Sign up as a Cadet, a Veteran Mentor, or both. Tell us your goals, areas and "
"timezone."
msgstr ""
"Inscrivez-vous comme Cadet, Mentor Vétéran, ou les deux. Indiquez-nous vos "
"objectifs, vos domaines et votre fuseau horaire."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Get matched"
msgstr "Trouver un binôme"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"The Grid suggests best-fit pairings by area, timezone and goals. You approve "
"— nobody is forced together."
msgstr ""
"The Grid suggère les meilleurs binômes par domaine, fuseau horaire et "
"objectifs. Vous approuvez — personne n'est forcé."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Run Field Exercises"
msgstr "Réaliser des Exercices de terrain"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"Work through a Track together — first fit, first fleet, first ratting site — "
"and debrief each one."
msgstr ""
"Parcourez un Parcours ensemble — premier fit, première flotte, premier site "
"de ratting — et débriefez chacun."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Earn recognition"
msgstr "Gagner de la reconnaissance"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"Completed exercises are validated, then Cadet and Mentor both collect their "
"rewards."
msgstr ""
"Les exercices terminés sont validés, puis le Cadet et le Mentor récupèrent "
"tous deux leurs récompenses."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "What you earn"
msgstr "Ce que vous gagnez"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"Progress is real recognition, not a participation ribbon. Depending on how "
"leadership has tuned the programme, completing exercises and certifications "
"can grant:"
msgstr ""
"La progression, c'est une vraie reconnaissance, pas une médaille de "
"participation. Selon la façon dont la direction a réglé le programme, "
"terminer des exercices et des certifications peut accorder :"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "ISK rewards"
msgstr "Récompenses en ISK"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"Direct payouts for milestones — for the Cadet who did the work and the "
"Mentor who taught it."
msgstr ""
"Paiements directs pour les jalons — pour le Cadet qui a fait le travail et "
"le Mentor qui l'a enseigné."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Points on the corp recognition ledger that count toward your standing."
msgstr ""
"Des points sur le registre de reconnaissance de la corpo qui comptent pour "
"votre classement."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Tiered mentor and cadet badges that show on your profile and dashboard."
msgstr ""
"Des badges de mentor et de cadet à paliers qui s'affichent sur votre profil "
"et votre tableau de bord."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Certifications"
msgstr "Certifications"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"Proof you can fly the doctrine, hold tackle, or lead a small gang — "
"recognised corp-wide."
msgstr ""
"La preuve que vous pouvez voler la doctrine, tenir le tackle ou mener un "
"petit gang — reconnu dans toute la corpo."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Honest validation &amp; privacy"
msgstr "Validation honnête &amp; confidentialité"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Some steps auto-check."
msgstr "Certaines étapes se vérifient automatiquement."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"Where the Grid can confirm a fact from EVE data — a skill trained, a ship "
"owned — it ticks the box for you."
msgstr ""
"Là où the Grid peut confirmer un fait à partir des données EVE — une skill "
"entraînée, un vaisseau possédé — il coche la case pour vous."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "The rest is a Mentor sign-off."
msgstr "Le reste est une validation du Mentor."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"Things a machine can't judge — \"did the debrief, showed up, gets it\" — "
"your Mentor confirms by hand. No gaming it."
msgstr ""
"Les choses qu'une machine ne peut juger — \"a fait le débriefing, était "
"présent, a compris\" — votre Mentor les confirme à la main. Impossible de "
"tricher."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "ESI is opt-in and minimal."
msgstr "L'ESI est facultatif et minimal."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid ""
"We only ask for a scope when an exercise genuinely needs it, and never more "
"than that. You can join and progress plenty without granting any."
msgstr ""
"Nous ne demandons un scope que lorsqu'un exercice en a réellement besoin, et "
"jamais plus. Vous pouvez rejoindre et bien progresser sans en accorder aucun."

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "Commitment:"
msgstr "Engagement :"

#: templates/mentorship/landing.html
msgid "a few hours a week is plenty — set your own pace, pause any time."
msgstr ""
"quelques heures par semaine suffisent — allez à votre rythme, faites une "
"pause quand vous voulez."

